00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.802 line:5%,start
ABBY (Voiceover):
Previously on "Dance Moms."

00:00:02.869 --> 00:00:05.271 line:5%,start
Your replacements will
be at the competition.

00:00:05.338 --> 00:00:09.075 line:5%,start
Could you quit running up to the mirror,
so close? Think!

00:00:09.142 --> 00:00:11.244 line:5%,start
Mackenzie forgets her dance on stage.

00:00:11.311 --> 00:00:13.680 line:5%,start
She goes completely blank.
Listen to what I'm saying.

00:00:13.747 --> 00:00:16.216 line:5%,start
- I'm hearing you. And I know.
- ABBY: Nothing should get in their way.

00:00:16.282 --> 00:00:19.586 line:5%,start
Same think about worrying
about a guy, instead of your own kids.

00:00:19.652 --> 00:00:21.321 line:5%,start
MELISSA: We have a happy household.

00:00:21.388 --> 00:00:23.723 line:5%,start
Well, your kid doesn't look
very happy to me. You are more worried

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:26.559 line:5%,start
about your friendships with all of
these women than your own kids

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.261 line:5%,start
and you know it, because you're an idiot!

00:00:28.628 --> 00:00:29.696 line:5%,start
Yeah, go.

00:00:29.763 --> 00:00:31.331 line:5%,start
ABBY (Voiceover) Coming up on "Dance Moms"

00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:33.433 line:5%,start
Jill, she did a costume
behind Abby's back.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:37.337 line:5%,start
I don't like people going behind my back.
You know that's my problem with Melissa.

00:00:37.404 --> 00:00:38.772 line:5%,start
You're using hats.

00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:43.143 line:5%,start
A hat is very specific to the style
of the routine.

00:00:43.209 --> 00:00:45.412 line:5%,start
Put the hat on their head
and make sure it's right.

00:00:45.478 --> 00:00:47.647 line:5%,start
Kendall, I don't think
you'll be doing your solo.

00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:49.816 line:5%,start
It's all their fault!
Get your kid and leave.

00:00:49.883 --> 00:00:51.451 line:5%,start
You're idiots if you stay.

00:00:51.518 --> 00:00:54.354 line:5%,start
I knew something was up when
we hadn't seen Cathy in weeks.

00:00:54.421 --> 00:00:56.423 line:5%,start
I don't want to be fourth
in front of Cathy.

00:00:56.589 --> 00:00:59.459 line:5%,start
The boys are just amazing.
[Christi] Come on, Chlo. We're done.

00:01:00.727 --> 00:01:02.896 line:95%,end
[theme music]

00:01:02.996 --> 00:01:04.330 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Get up.

00:01:04.431 --> 00:01:06.232 line:95%,end
Get on the floor.

00:01:06.332 --> 00:01:11.971 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls,
living on the dance floor.

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:15.909 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:01:21.781 --> 00:01:24.417 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I don't think I've ever been
so nervous to walk into pyramid

00:01:24.484 --> 00:01:25.518 line:95%,end
as I am right now.

00:01:25.585 --> 00:01:28.188 line:5%,start
It's bad enough that we got fourth place
at competition last week

00:01:28.254 --> 00:01:31.424 line:95%,end
but Abby and I got in a big fight.
And I know she's mad at me.

00:01:35.829 --> 00:01:37.964 line:95%,end
I just want to look at
what fourth place looks like.

00:01:38.965 --> 00:01:40.100 line:95%,end
I really can't remember

00:01:40.166 --> 00:01:43.903 line:5%,start
when the Abby Lee Dance Company
competition team came in fourth.

00:01:44.337 --> 00:01:47.140 line:95%,end
That had to be 20, 25 years ago.

00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:48.341 line:95%,end
It was devastating to me.

00:01:48.408 --> 00:01:52.812 line:95%,end
This weekend we will be traveling
to Voorhees, New Jersey.

00:01:53.413 --> 00:01:56.082 line:95%,end
We will be attending On Stage America.

00:01:56.149 --> 00:01:57.851 line:95%,end
I don't want to be fourth, again.

00:01:58.551 --> 00:02:01.087 line:95%,end
On the bottom, Mackenzie.

00:02:01.154 --> 00:02:04.023 line:95%,end
You will not be performing in
the group routine this weekend.

00:02:05.191 --> 00:02:07.527 line:95%,end
Next, Maddie.

00:02:07.594 --> 00:02:10.130 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Maddie and Mackenzie
we're both at the bottom.

00:02:10.196 --> 00:02:11.464 line:95%,end
It was, you know, a little different.

00:02:11.531 --> 00:02:15.135 line:95%,end
It is what it is. I mean, I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

00:02:15.201 --> 00:02:18.638 line:95%,end
ABBY: At Nationals you were
amazing, just as good as Chloe.

00:02:18.705 --> 00:02:19.873 line:95%,end
But Chloe won.

00:02:19.939 --> 00:02:21.541 line:95%,end
And ever since then...

00:02:22.709 --> 00:02:24.377 line:95%,end
KELLY: I think Melissa and Maddie need

00:02:24.444 --> 00:02:27.180 line:5%,start
to get used to taking a turn
at the bottom.

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:28.448 line:5%,start
Because we've all been there.

00:02:29.949 --> 00:02:33.686 line:95%,end
Paige, once again, it's
the same pattern, Kelly.

00:02:33.753 --> 00:02:35.555 line:95%,end
It's like she doesn't
have to work anymore.

00:02:35.622 --> 00:02:37.824 line:95%,end
Like, I went, I won.
Third was good enough for me.

00:02:41.261 --> 00:02:45.532 line:95%,end
Nia, you're doing fine. But is fine
going to make you a star?

00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:52.038 line:95%,end
Kendall, you didn't pull
my eyes in a negative way.

00:02:52.205 --> 00:02:54.040 line:95%,end
You actually pulled
them in a positive way.

00:02:54.107 --> 00:02:58.978 line:95%,end
When I don't say your name and
I stop yelling at you, get worried.

00:02:59.546 --> 00:03:03.016 line:5%,start
JILL: I'm ecstatic because Kendall's never
been off the bottom row of the pyramid.

00:03:03.082 --> 00:03:06.452 line:95%,end
We're moving up. This is what
we're working towards. This is good.

00:03:06.519 --> 00:03:11.024 line:95%,end
And, Chloe, I thought you looked great.
It was good.

00:03:11.090 --> 00:03:13.893 line:95%,end
Was that exactly what you're
supposed to do? No.

00:03:13.960 --> 00:03:17.363 line:95%,end
Go out there and do the
routine that you were taught

00:03:17.430 --> 00:03:19.265 line:95%,end
the way I envision it.

00:03:19.332 --> 00:03:23.036 line:95%,end
Better yet, Chloe, do it
better than I can imagine it.

00:03:23.536 --> 00:03:24.837 line:95%,end
That's a dancer.

00:03:25.004 --> 00:03:26.306 line:95%,end
And, on top of the pyramid...

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:28.775 line:95%,end
I think the kids think
it's going to be Brooke.


00:03:28.841 --> 00:03:31.010 line:95%,end
Ha! Not a chance.

00:03:32.579 --> 00:03:33.613 line:95%,end
is nobody.

00:03:35.315 --> 00:03:38.384 line:95%,end
Nobody in a group that got
fourth deserves that spot.

00:03:38.851 --> 00:03:40.520 line:95%,end
Brooke, I don't have you on the team.

00:03:40.587 --> 00:03:42.055 line:95%,end
KELLY: She's been here every week.

00:03:42.121 --> 00:03:44.057 line:95%,end
What is the purpose of
her coming every week

00:03:44.123 --> 00:03:45.491 line:95%,end
if you're not going
to put her on the pyramid?

00:03:46.025 --> 00:03:47.927 line:95%,end
Brooke, do you want to be here?

00:03:49.295 --> 00:03:52.966 line:95%,end
See, that to me is not a
response that I'm looking for.

00:03:53.032 --> 00:03:57.070 line:95%,end
KELLY: I've been playing by the rules
with Abby. I haven't been name calling.

00:03:57.136 --> 00:04:00.306 line:95%,end
I haven't been fighting with her and
Abby still won't put her on the pyramid.

00:04:00.373 --> 00:04:02.141 line:95%,end
It's like she's playing a game with me.

00:04:02.208 --> 00:04:05.578 line:95%,end
I really don't care because I think your
pyramid is a crock of [bleep] anyways.

00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:09.249 line:95%,end
This weekend we are doing a group routine
called "Pink Lemonade."

00:04:09.315 --> 00:04:11.551 line:95%,end
Brooke, I plan for you
to be in the group routine.

00:04:12.285 --> 00:04:14.621 line:95%,end
Kendall, you have a solo.

00:04:15.054 --> 00:04:16.155 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:04:16.222 --> 00:04:19.859 line:95%,end
Your solo is entitled "Owe You Nothing."

00:04:20.526 --> 00:04:21.561 line:95%,end
Remember that.

00:04:21.628 --> 00:04:23.529 line:95%,end
I owe you nothing.

00:04:24.230 --> 00:04:25.431 line:95%,end
You are very lucky.

00:04:25.498 --> 00:04:28.534 line:95%,end
Embrace this opportunity
and make the most of it.

00:04:29.502 --> 00:04:31.471 line:95%,end
Nia, you also have a solo.

00:04:31.537 --> 00:04:33.373 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:04:33.473 --> 00:04:36.609 line:95%,end
Your solo is entitled
"100 Years From Now."

00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:40.613 line:95%,end
Is it going to take you 100 more
years to straighten those legs

00:04:40.713 --> 00:04:44.017 line:95%,end
and point those feet or
are you going to do it now?

00:04:44.484 --> 00:04:45.518 line:95%,end
And I have one more solo.

00:04:47.687 --> 00:04:49.889 line:95%,end
Chloe, do you think you can
do the dance that I teach you?

00:04:51.991 --> 00:04:54.794 line:95%,end
Have you talked to your mom
about stopping the advocacy

00:04:54.861 --> 00:04:55.995 line:95%,end
for all the other mothers?

00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:58.698 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: It's obvious that
Abby is still holding a grudge

00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:00.333 line:5%,start
over our walk out a few weeks ago.

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:02.502 line:95%,end
Well, we're here now, and
Chloe's ready to work.

00:05:02.568 --> 00:05:03.970 line:95%,end
And Abby just needs to move on.

00:05:04.537 --> 00:05:08.107 line:95%,end
Chloe, this is a contemporary routine,
as well.

00:05:08.174 --> 00:05:12.645 line:95%,end
There's lots of hits, accents, it's
stronger than you've been doing before.

00:05:12.712 --> 00:05:15.148 line:95%,end
And it is called "Left in the Dark."

00:05:15.682 --> 00:05:18.284 line:95%,end
The group routine is entitled
"Pink Lemonade."

00:05:18.685 --> 00:05:22.422 line:95%,end
You're using hats, and
the hats are a prop.

00:05:22.588 --> 00:05:25.591 line:95%,end
Drop your hat and you're off the team.

00:05:25.758 --> 00:05:28.161 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:31.030 line:95%,end
[laughter]
KELLY: God! Let's be a little harsh.

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:32.498 line:95%,end
They think I'm joking?

00:05:32.565 --> 00:05:35.835 line:95%,end
Let somebody drop the
hat and see what happens.

00:05:35.902 --> 00:05:38.971 line:95%,end
Moms, you're dismissed.
You're going to be rhinestoning.

00:05:39.038 --> 00:05:42.442 line:95%,end
Ladies, spread apart. Start to warm up.
Grand pliÃ© in second.

00:05:44.277 --> 00:05:46.346 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:05:47.547 --> 00:05:48.648 line:5%,start
(singing) The world...

00:05:48.715 --> 00:05:53.152 line:5%,start
The world was mine to give.

00:05:54.654 --> 00:05:57.156 line:95%,end
I must say, I'm surprised that Abby's up.

00:05:57.223 --> 00:05:59.292 line:95%,end
Abby must really care about this routine.

00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:01.728 line:95%,end
She is actually up and out of her chair.

00:06:01.794 --> 00:06:04.530 line:95%,end
Straddle leap, cut under, two jumps.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:10.436 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:06:11.003 --> 00:06:13.539 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Melissa, did Abby apologize to you?

00:06:13.639 --> 00:06:16.175 line:95%,end
No. Has she ever apologized to you?

00:06:16.342 --> 00:06:19.145 line:95%,end
JILL: Maddie and Mackenzie are both
at the bottom of the pyramid.

00:06:19.212 --> 00:06:21.881 line:95%,end
And I know Melissa is about to explode.

00:06:22.548 --> 00:06:26.586 line:95%,end
Clearly Abby, at this point,
wants nothing to do with Melissa.

00:06:26.652 --> 00:06:29.455 line:95%,end
It surprised me that she
said all that stuff to you

00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:32.191 line:95%,end
and you did not say anything back to her.

00:06:33.025 --> 00:06:35.561 line:95%,end
You are more worried about
your friendships with all these women

00:06:35.628 --> 00:06:37.597 line:95%,end
than your own kids, and you know it.

00:06:37.663 --> 00:06:41.834 line:95%,end
Same thing about worrying about
a guy instead of your own kids! Yes!

00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:44.270 line:95%,end
Going from one husband to another

00:06:44.337 --> 00:06:46.973 line:95%,end
instead of just worrying
about your kids... please.

00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:48.741 line:95%,end
It is what it is.

00:06:48.808 --> 00:06:51.978 line:95%,end
If somebody said that stuff about me
I don't know how I couldn't say something.

00:06:52.044 --> 00:06:54.380 line:95%,end
That's-- that's-- it works for you,
I guess. You know?

00:06:54.447 --> 00:06:56.516 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: It's so funny to
me to see Melissa sit there

00:06:56.582 --> 00:06:58.618 line:95%,end
and be like, "Oh, I don't care
if Maddie doesn't have a solo."


00:06:58.684 --> 00:07:00.720 line:95%,end
She's like, "No, I don't even care."

00:07:00.787 --> 00:07:02.321 line:95%,end
Melissa's wearing glasses this week

00:07:02.388 --> 00:07:04.857 line:95%,end
because her contacts can't stand through
all those tears.

00:07:04.924 --> 00:07:08.628 line:95%,end
You sat there and did not say a word and
Maddie still didn't get a solo this week.

00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:13.299 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I'm not saying
anything to her about it.

00:07:13.366 --> 00:07:15.902 line:95%,end
That's not anybody else's concern.

00:07:15.968 --> 00:07:18.237 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:07:22.809 --> 00:07:26.312 line:5%,start
CATHY: You are here because
I had a team last year.

00:07:26.379 --> 00:07:31.951 line:5%,start
I was a little lenient with that team
and it bit me in the apples.

00:07:32.018 --> 00:07:36.456 line:5%,start
I haven't seen Abby since
last year's Nationals in LA.

00:07:36.522 --> 00:07:41.160 line:95%,end
Since that time, I've used all my
resources to get just that perfect team.

00:07:41.227 --> 00:07:43.596 line:95%,end
And I think I finally have it.

00:07:44.730 --> 00:07:46.265 line:95%,end
It's all boys.

00:07:47.533 --> 00:07:48.668 line:95%,end
That's genius.

00:07:48.734 --> 00:07:52.405 line:95%,end
There's a dance teacher by
the name of Abby Lee Miller.

00:07:52.805 --> 00:07:53.806 line:5%,start
I need to win.

00:07:53.873 --> 00:07:55.641 line:5%,start
I need to beat her.

00:07:55.808 --> 00:07:57.109 line:5%,start
That's why you guys are here.

00:07:57.677 --> 00:08:00.813 line:95%,end
First we have Bryant.

00:08:01.314 --> 00:08:03.950 line:95%,end
I know you're going to have to
really focus on your technique,

00:08:04.016 --> 00:08:06.219 line:95%,end
but I think you have a
burning desire to get ahead.

00:08:06.385 --> 00:08:08.054 line:95%,end
- Yes?
- Yeah.

00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.322 line:95%,end
Jalen.

00:08:09.388 --> 00:08:12.925 line:95%,end
If there's a B-boy to
be had, he's the one.

00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:17.463 line:95%,end
If you want to slide on your head right
past Abby Miller, you do that.

00:08:19.065 --> 00:08:21.334 line:95%,end
Gino, you've got excellent technique.

00:08:21.901 --> 00:08:24.737 line:95%,end
I know that you're going
to bring it to the board.

00:08:24.804 --> 00:08:27.240 line:95%,end
And at the top of the pyramid...

00:08:28.274 --> 00:08:33.513 line:95%,end
Zack, highly trained, excellent technique.

00:08:33.913 --> 00:08:37.617 line:95%,end
And I a certain teacher
by the name of Abby Miller

00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:41.521 line:95%,end
who invited you
to come dance with her team.

00:08:41.888 --> 00:08:44.190 line:95%,end
So here we have it. Yes?

00:08:44.257 --> 00:08:45.424 line:95%,end
My thoughts behind the pyramid...

00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:49.161 line:95%,end
it promotes individual as
opposed to a group effort.

00:08:49.228 --> 00:08:53.266 line:95%,end
You're right.
And team, individual, leader.

00:08:53.432 --> 00:08:55.034 line:95%,end
- Enough said.
- MAN: We'll see.

00:08:55.201 --> 00:08:56.569 line:95%,end
OK, guys, let's go.

00:08:56.636 --> 00:08:59.539 line:95%,end
Girls are a dime a dozen at competitions.

00:08:59.705 --> 00:09:02.642 line:95%,end
Boys make the judges
sit up and take notice

00:09:02.808 --> 00:09:06.612 line:95%,end
especially when the
boys are as technically

00:09:06.679 --> 00:09:09.782 line:95%,end
fabulous as the boys that I've found.

00:09:09.949 --> 00:09:13.219 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:17.723 line:95%,end
ABBY: The name of the song is
"Pink Lemonade", but it's about life.

00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:20.526 line:95%,end
You get lemons, you make lemonade.

00:09:20.593 --> 00:09:21.961 line:95%,end
OK, let's try that with the music.

00:09:22.495 --> 00:09:25.498 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Maddie looks like
she's ready to lose her mind.

00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:28.501 line:95%,end
I don't know how much more of this Melissa
is going to be able to take.

00:09:28.668 --> 00:09:31.737 line:95%,end
Because Maddie doesn't have a solo,
Mackenzie's not even in the group dance.

00:09:31.837 --> 00:09:33.372 line:95%,end
She's over in the corner
like a little rat, like,

00:09:33.839 --> 00:09:36.642 line:95%,end
"Oh, go in the corner, Kenz.
Blah, blah, blah, blah."

00:09:38.277 --> 00:09:41.847 line:5%,start
Drag, ball change, hop,
chainÃ©, hold your head on.

00:09:42.014 --> 00:09:44.984 line:95%,end
Arms, arms, arms.

00:09:48.654 --> 00:09:50.690 line:95%,end
HOLLY: What are you
going to do about Abby?

00:09:50.856 --> 00:09:52.358 line:95%,end
You're not going to do anything, really?

00:09:52.458 --> 00:09:53.859 line:95%,end
I don't know what to do.

00:09:54.026 --> 00:09:56.495 line:95%,end
I mean, I-- you know, it's a
shame that my whole kid's life

00:09:56.662 --> 00:09:57.763 line:95%,end
is about Miss Abby.

00:09:57.830 --> 00:09:59.632 line:95%,end
And I don't want to hurt Abby's feelings.

00:09:59.765 --> 00:10:01.500 line:95%,end
I'm not one to confront people.

00:10:01.634 --> 00:10:04.537 line:95%,end
I'll always appreciate everything
that Abby has done for my children.

00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:08.374 line:95%,end
She has made my children into the dancers
that they've become.

00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:09.642 line:95%,end
I'm going to be honest with you.

00:10:09.742 --> 00:10:12.778 line:95%,end
I regret things and I you know, I...

00:10:12.945 --> 00:10:15.247 line:95%,end
- I do.
- Like being in the car?

00:10:15.314 --> 00:10:16.882 line:95%,end
Do you regret that? I do.

00:10:16.949 --> 00:10:19.418 line:95%,end
Abby could turn on
anyone at any given time.

00:10:19.885 --> 00:10:21.454 line:95%,end
I'm sorry, but I do.


00:10:25.558 --> 00:10:26.759 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:10:26.826 --> 00:10:29.161 line:5%,start
- JEN: Hi. Great. Sure.
- Hi, Jen. Come on in.

00:10:29.261 --> 00:10:31.030 line:95%,end
This is going to be
a big week for Kendall.

00:10:31.097 --> 00:10:34.934 line:5%,start
She's getting a solo, so I
want her to look amazing.

00:10:35.568 --> 00:10:36.736 line:5%,start
Kendall, this is Jen.

00:10:36.802 --> 00:10:38.838 line:5%,start
- Hi. Hi. Nice to met you.
- Nice to meet you, Kendall.

00:10:38.904 --> 00:10:42.208 line:95%,end
- We want something over the top.
- Boom.

00:10:42.274 --> 00:10:45.544 line:95%,end
JILL: I know that Abby says a
costume doesn't make a number,

00:10:45.611 --> 00:10:46.979 line:95%,end
but it helps.

00:10:47.079 --> 00:10:49.815 line:95%,end
And if I'm willing to pay
the money and spend the time

00:10:49.882 --> 00:10:52.918 line:95%,end
and hire a designer, Abby
won't be able to overlook her.

00:10:52.985 --> 00:10:54.920 line:95%,end
- Bye.
- Bye. Thanks.

00:10:55.087 --> 00:10:57.023 line:95%,end
What do you think? Good.

00:10:57.089 --> 00:10:59.492 line:95%,end
It's going to be exciting! I'm so excited!

00:10:59.558 --> 00:11:00.693 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:02.928 line:95%,end
ABBY: Come on, girls!
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

00:11:02.995 --> 00:11:04.397 line:95%,end
Girls, listen up.

00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:08.367 line:5%,start
"Pink Lemonade" better not
be fourth or third or second.

00:11:08.567 --> 00:11:09.635 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:11:09.702 --> 00:11:12.304 line:5%,start
When you drag your foot from straddle
around, you're sickling your right foot.

00:11:12.405 --> 00:11:16.142 line:95%,end
This week we're doing a musical theater
number to "Pink Lemonade."

00:11:16.208 --> 00:11:19.545 line:95%,end
Chloe, you're flexing your
palms on the arch back.

00:11:19.712 --> 00:11:21.013 line:95%,end
The hands are clean.

00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:22.882 line:95%,end
Now the girls use hats.

00:11:22.948 --> 00:11:25.718 line:95%,end
And there's a little surprise
with the hats as the routine goes on.

00:11:25.785 --> 00:11:29.221 line:5%,start
They pull the hats off, the
hair comes tumbling all down

00:11:29.655 --> 00:11:33.092 line:95%,end
and then they continue to dance
with the hat in their hand.

00:11:33.259 --> 00:11:35.828 line:95%,end
Get That hat! Get it! Get it! Get it!

00:11:38.464 --> 00:11:39.799 line:95%,end
Nobody was good.

00:11:39.865 --> 00:11:42.968 line:95%,end
I mean, if that kid drops their hat
on stage, it ruins the whole number.

00:11:43.035 --> 00:11:47.273 line:95%,end
This is turning, leaping, jumping.
Not one person can be off.

00:11:47.339 --> 00:11:49.909 line:95%,end
Because when that hat's
off, you're going to see it.

00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:52.578 line:95%,end
Dancing with the hat is pretty hard.

00:11:52.645 --> 00:11:54.847 line:5%,start
I just hope that I don't
screw up at the competition.

00:11:54.914 --> 00:11:57.149 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:11:58.584 --> 00:12:01.654 line:95%,end
Yay! There we go. Good girl. Good girl.

00:12:01.754 --> 00:12:02.988 line:95%,end
Let's find you a cup.

00:12:03.456 --> 00:12:06.525 line:95%,end
JILL: Wow. You're all clean.

00:12:06.625 --> 00:12:07.927 line:95%,end
Look. She's like, I don't know.

00:12:07.993 --> 00:12:10.463 line:95%,end
She's going to know you
because you're my dog sitter today.

00:12:10.529 --> 00:12:14.533 line:95%,end
Jill is kind of, you know, stepping
into Melissa's old spot.

00:12:14.700 --> 00:12:16.402 line:95%,end
And she wants to be helpful.

00:12:16.469 --> 00:12:19.038 line:95%,end
Get the pooper scooper. Let's be helpful.

00:12:19.105 --> 00:12:20.840 line:95%,end
- You going to walk her for me?
- Outside?

00:12:21.006 --> 00:12:22.108 line:95%,end
- Yes.
- JILL: No, I don't...

00:12:22.274 --> 00:12:24.844 line:95%,end
Kendall doesn't come first.
My dog comes first.

00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:26.278 line:95%,end
So you want to go tinkles?

00:12:26.378 --> 00:12:28.280 line:95%,end
JILL: I'm honored that Abby
trusts her dog with me.

00:12:28.647 --> 00:12:31.984 line:95%,end
I just really hope she doesn't
go to doggie heaven on my watch.

00:12:32.151 --> 00:12:34.553 line:95%,end
Ooh, look, we have progress.
That's a good girl.

00:12:34.620 --> 00:12:36.222 line:95%,end
Go potty. Come on.

00:12:36.288 --> 00:12:39.325 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: I think Jill ye saw
an opening on Abby's pyramid

00:12:39.492 --> 00:12:41.994 line:5%,start
of moms and she's like, oh,
Melissa's fallen from grace.

00:12:42.161 --> 00:12:44.997 line:95%,end
I will walk the dog so I can be
at the top of the mom pyramid.

00:12:45.164 --> 00:12:46.966 line:95%,end
Come on. Come see your mama.

00:12:47.032 --> 00:12:48.968 line:95%,end
MELISSA: She'll bark when she sees her.

00:12:49.468 --> 00:12:50.803 line:95%,end
I bark when I see Abby, too.

00:12:50.903 --> 00:12:51.904 line:95%,end
[barking]

00:12:51.971 --> 00:12:53.305 line:95%,end
- MELISSA: See?
- I told you.

00:12:53.472 --> 00:12:56.342 line:95%,end
JILL: I know! You saw her.

00:12:57.109 --> 00:12:59.345 line:95%,end
I guess Broadway Baby can sense evil, too.

00:12:59.512 --> 00:13:01.347 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:13:03.516 --> 00:13:04.583 line:95%,end
We're going to start right here.

00:13:04.683 --> 00:13:07.052 line:5%,start
Remember, this is "Owe You Nothing."

00:13:07.219 --> 00:13:10.055 line:5%,start
You're like, I don't owe you.

00:13:10.122 --> 00:13:14.393 line:95%,end
You're more, like, dangerous. Boom.

00:13:15.528 --> 00:13:17.530 line:95%,end
Kendall is doing a jazz acrobatic routine.

00:13:17.596 --> 00:13:19.732 line:95%,end
It's entitled "Owe You Nothing."

00:13:19.899 --> 00:13:22.101 line:95%,end
Take the arms down the body.

00:13:22.268 --> 00:13:24.236 line:95%,end
Push like there's a wall
on either side of you.

00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:27.473 line:95%,end
And, you know what?
No more second chances, Kendall.

00:13:27.540 --> 00:13:31.277 line:95%,end
Has anybody ever heard
of this girl, Jen Rocket?

00:13:31.377 --> 00:13:34.446 line:95%,end
I had her come over
because I don't have costumes

00:13:34.513 --> 00:13:38.784 line:95%,end
that haven't been worn with Abby
that aren't another studio's. So I...

00:13:38.851 --> 00:13:41.921 line:95%,end
Did Abby design it or
did she leave it up to you to design it?

00:13:42.388 --> 00:13:44.256 line:95%,end
No, Abby didn't design it.

00:13:44.423 --> 00:13:47.493 line:95%,end
- [gasps] You're going to get in trouble.
- JILL: She had told me what she wanted.


00:13:47.593 --> 00:13:51.197 line:95%,end
Because I don't want you to get yelled
at for doing something behind her back.

00:13:51.530 --> 00:13:53.532 line:95%,end
- ABBY: Moms!
- MELISSA: Yes?

00:13:53.699 --> 00:13:56.535 line:95%,end
Come on down to the costume shop.
I want to go over these rhinestones.

00:13:56.635 --> 00:13:57.736 line:95%,end
- JILL: Woo-hoo!
- Let's go.

00:13:57.803 --> 00:13:59.738 line:95%,end
Let's get it done so we can
get home early and pack.

00:13:59.905 --> 00:14:01.774 line:95%,end
Yeah, OK. That's never going to happen.

00:14:01.841 --> 00:14:03.709 line:95%,end
ABBY: The costumes were custom made.

00:14:03.776 --> 00:14:06.579 line:95%,end
They're ready for the girls.
All they need is rhinestones.

00:14:06.645 --> 00:14:10.816 line:95%,end
The fedora is to be worn like that.

00:14:10.883 --> 00:14:13.953 line:95%,end
So it sits, it's all in
my head and I'm pointing it

00:14:14.119 --> 00:14:15.421 line:95%,end
to the right and down.

00:14:15.487 --> 00:14:17.923 line:95%,end
I have a costume in my
dancewear store for Nia.

00:14:18.023 --> 00:14:20.659 line:95%,end
Obviously, Chloe is going
to wear a ragdoll costume.

00:14:20.759 --> 00:14:24.496 line:95%,end
All right, now Kendall, for that solo
I would have loved her to be in green.

00:14:24.663 --> 00:14:27.366 line:95%,end
Well, let me tell you,
and regarding the costume

00:14:27.433 --> 00:14:30.269 line:95%,end
I have gray bottoms and a gray top.

00:14:30.402 --> 00:14:33.439 line:95%,end
And it's going to have,
like, a lace overlay over it.

00:14:33.505 --> 00:14:34.807 line:95%,end
You know what, Abby?

00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:36.775 line:95%,end
I think you're going to
like what we came up.

00:14:36.842 --> 00:14:40.746 line:95%,end
Jill, you just have to understand,
I don't like people going behind my back.

00:14:40.946 --> 00:14:41.947 line:95%,end
I wouldn't go behind your back, Abby.

00:14:42.014 --> 00:14:44.250 line:95%,end
But you know that's my
problem with Melissa.

00:14:44.316 --> 00:14:48.153 line:95%,end
JILL: I see and feel the tension
between Abby and Melissa.

00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:50.589 line:95%,end
And I know that Abby is
used to Melissa doing

00:14:50.723 --> 00:14:52.725 line:95%,end
all these extra things for her.

00:14:52.791 --> 00:14:55.294 line:95%,end
But Abby is not asking her to do it.

00:14:55.461 --> 00:14:57.630 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I guess Jill is taking
the approach

00:14:57.696 --> 00:15:01.433 line:95%,end
that gifts didn't really get her too far
so now she's into doing favors for Abby.

00:15:01.500 --> 00:15:02.902 line:95%,end
MELISSA: That's something I would do.

00:15:03.335 --> 00:15:05.170 line:95%,end
Is there anything else in
here you need me to do for you?

00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:07.106 line:95%,end
- Nope.
- You don't need any help in here?

00:15:07.172 --> 00:15:08.841 line:95%,end
No. We're all good. All right.

00:15:11.277 --> 00:15:13.379 line:95%,end
- CHRISTI: Did you start your solo?
- No?

00:15:14.113 --> 00:15:15.147 line:5%,start
Whatever.

00:15:16.649 --> 00:15:17.883 line:5%,start
I don't, either.

00:15:18.050 --> 00:15:21.387 line:5%,start
Nia, I told you before, the name of
your routine is "100 Years From Now."

00:15:21.453 --> 00:15:24.657 line:95%,end
You don't have 100 years from now
to fix your feet and your legs

00:15:24.723 --> 00:15:27.559 line:95%,end
I'm giving Nia a solo.
You might think I'm off my rocker.

00:15:27.726 --> 00:15:29.762 line:95%,end
This kid keeps telling me
she's working on her legs

00:15:29.862 --> 00:15:31.830 line:95%,end
and working on her feet
and working on her turnout.

00:15:31.897 --> 00:15:34.166 line:95%,end
I want to see her do a lyrical solo.

00:15:34.233 --> 00:15:36.802 line:95%,end
This is a lyrical routine
in the 11-12 age group.

00:15:36.869 --> 00:15:37.903 line:95%,end
Step it up!

00:15:38.404 --> 00:15:41.040 line:95%,end
- You all right?
- No. I'm not.

00:15:41.206 --> 00:15:43.509 line:95%,end
- What's wrong?
- My daughter hasn't started her solo.

00:15:43.609 --> 00:15:44.877 line:95%,end
Nobody seems to care.

00:15:45.044 --> 00:15:47.379 line:95%,end
Christi, maybe this is Abby's test

00:15:47.446 --> 00:15:49.715 line:95%,end
when she talks about
advocating for your child.

00:15:49.882 --> 00:15:51.917 line:95%,end
Holly can't possibly
understand how I'm feeling.

00:15:51.984 --> 00:15:54.620 line:95%,end
Nia's solo is finished, and
Chloe hasn't even started hers.

00:15:54.687 --> 00:15:57.022 line:95%,end
Why does Nia need all
that more time than Chloe?

00:15:57.089 --> 00:15:58.991 line:95%,end
Maybe you just need to go
down there and just talk to Ab.

00:15:59.058 --> 00:16:01.493 line:95%,end
OK, no. I don't know if you've met Abby.

00:16:01.660 --> 00:16:04.330 line:95%,end
She doesn't have conversations.
She argues.

00:16:04.396 --> 00:16:05.998 line:95%,end
I wasn't trying to suggest
that you should fight with her.

00:16:06.065 --> 00:16:07.533 line:95%,end
- OK, thanks.
- OK.

00:16:07.599 --> 00:16:09.234 line:95%,end
You know have to get snippy with me, miss.

00:16:09.401 --> 00:16:12.237 line:95%,end
I feel like Christi's overreacting
more and more these days.

00:16:12.304 --> 00:16:14.006 line:5%,start
She's constantly throwing tantrums

00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:15.941 line:5%,start
and I'm not in the mood to fuss over her.

00:16:16.241 --> 00:16:17.609 line:95%,end
Yes, Hello?

00:16:17.710 --> 00:16:20.746 line:95%,end
Yes. This is Abby Lee from the
Abby Lee Dance Company

00:16:20.913 --> 00:16:22.047 line:95%,end
in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.

00:16:22.181 --> 00:16:24.516 line:95%,end
We're attending your event
in Voorhees, New Jersey.

00:16:24.683 --> 00:16:27.386 line:95%,end
I had to call the competition to verify

00:16:27.453 --> 00:16:29.722 line:95%,end
that our routines were entered
in the correct categories.

00:16:30.055 --> 00:16:32.992 line:95%,end
And I asked if anybody was
coming from another state.

00:16:33.058 --> 00:16:34.860 line:95%,end
I talked to On Stage America.

00:16:34.927 --> 00:16:36.261 line:95%,end
She wouldn't give me names

00:16:36.762 --> 00:16:39.865 line:95%,end
but there was one student from
Pennsylvania, which is us

00:16:40.299 --> 00:16:43.602 line:95%,end
and one studio from Ohio.

00:16:43.669 --> 00:16:47.206 line:95%,end
That's not just any studio from Ohio.
That's got to be Cathy.

00:16:47.706 --> 00:16:51.243 line:95%,end
She's going to come back with a vengeance.
I didn't like being fourth last week.

00:16:51.777 --> 00:16:54.079 line:95%,end
I don't want to be
fourth in front of Cathy.

00:16:54.246 --> 00:16:58.384 line:95%,end
The girls have to have straight legs.
Their arms need to be placed correctly.

00:16:58.450 --> 00:16:59.718 line:95%,end
They have to nail those turns.

00:16:59.785 --> 00:17:01.920 line:95%,end
If they don't win I get
to say, "I told you so."


00:17:07.626 --> 00:17:09.428 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:17:09.495 --> 00:17:13.032 line:5%,start
And, a one, two, one, two, three.

00:17:13.098 --> 00:17:16.668 line:5%,start
And a one, two, and one, two, three.

00:17:17.236 --> 00:17:18.437 line:95%,end
I like this. This is cool.

00:17:18.504 --> 00:17:19.805 line:95%,end
- But I like this.
- Boom.

00:17:19.872 --> 00:17:20.939 line:95%,end
That, right there.

00:17:21.006 --> 00:17:24.109 line:95%,end
As I'm watching Chloe dance, she's really
done on this creepy doll thing well.

00:17:24.176 --> 00:17:28.213 line:5%,start
And, more importantly, she's remembering
every bit of her choreography

00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:29.648 line:95%,end
with so little time to practice.

00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:32.451 line:95%,end
Feel that? Slow down. Do it again.

00:17:32.518 --> 00:17:34.253 line:95%,end
- And...
- MELISSA: This is pretty.

00:17:34.319 --> 00:17:37.222 line:95%,end
- Excuse me. Chloe's costume is beautiful.
MELISSA: Yes, it is.

00:17:37.289 --> 00:17:39.058 line:95%,end
- JILL: Beautiful. You did great job.
- CHRISTI: I'm not done.

00:17:39.591 --> 00:17:40.759 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Jill, what are you doing?

00:17:40.826 --> 00:17:42.194 line:95%,end
Are you not using the
costume that lady made?

00:17:42.261 --> 00:17:43.962 line:95%,end
Yeah. She wants green in
it, so I'm going to try

00:17:44.029 --> 00:17:46.031 line:95%,end
to get some green pieces to put in it.

00:17:46.098 --> 00:17:49.668 line:95%,end
- Did you show her the picture of it?
- No.

00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:52.805 line:5%,start
KELLY: Abby asked everyone
to have their costumes done for today.

00:17:52.905 --> 00:17:56.708 line:5%,start
Like, I can't believe
Jill doesn't have hers.

00:17:56.775 --> 00:17:58.143 line:95%,end
Jill, I'm confused.

00:17:58.210 --> 00:18:01.513 line:95%,end
You don't have a costume for Kendall,
but I thought you had one made.

00:18:01.580 --> 00:18:03.749 line:95%,end
I don't have it. That was yesterday.

00:18:03.816 --> 00:18:06.852 line:95%,end
- Oh, well, what are you working on now?
- Oh. This is pieces for the costume.

00:18:06.919 --> 00:18:08.687 line:95%,end
- CHRISTI: Okay.
- JILL: I don't have it in my possession.

00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:10.255 line:95%,end
And then you're just going
to add those pieces...

00:18:10.355 --> 00:18:11.824 line:95%,end
- And then I was going to add this.
- Oh, OK.

00:18:11.957 --> 00:18:13.592 line:95%,end
I was just a little confused.

00:18:13.759 --> 00:18:15.761 line:95%,end
Jill's been here long enough
that you would think

00:18:15.828 --> 00:18:19.098 line:95%,end
she would be smart enough to know
you just don't do stuff like that.

00:18:19.164 --> 00:18:21.733 line:95%,end
music playing]

00:18:24.136 --> 00:18:26.839 line:5%,start
They're so holding back
because of their hats.

00:18:26.905 --> 00:18:28.607 line:95%,end
I was thinking the same thing.

00:18:28.707 --> 00:18:30.976 line:95%,end
They can't go all-out
because they've got to hold their heads

00:18:31.043 --> 00:18:32.644 line:95%,end
a certain way so the hats don't fall off.

00:18:32.711 --> 00:18:34.246 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Mm-hmm.
Chloe was saying that before, last night.

00:18:34.313 --> 00:18:36.248 line:95%,end
So they're dancing kind of stiff, I think.

00:18:36.315 --> 00:18:37.316 line:95%,end
Slow down, there.

00:18:37.382 --> 00:18:40.452 line:95%,end
Brooke, you're never straightening out
your first leg in that jump, at all.

00:18:40.519 --> 00:18:42.721 line:95%,end
Make sure your hat's on your head.

00:18:42.888 --> 00:18:45.190 line:5%,start
We all learned, at the very
first competition

00:18:45.257 --> 00:18:47.693 line:5%,start
that we ever went to with this
particular team

00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:50.395 line:95%,end
that the headpiece stays on your head.

00:18:50.462 --> 00:18:52.898 line:95%,end
Who did we learn it from? Chloe.

00:18:52.998 --> 00:18:54.333 line:95%,end
I'm totally serious.

00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.502 line:95%,end
I mean, if that kid
drops their hat onstage

00:18:56.668 --> 00:18:57.803 line:95%,end
it ruins the whole number.

00:18:57.903 --> 00:19:00.439 line:95%,end
All the judges are going
to look at somebody's hat.

00:19:01.073 --> 00:19:02.541 line:95%,end
All right, ladies! [gasps]

00:19:02.641 --> 00:19:03.675 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Scared me.

00:19:03.742 --> 00:19:05.477 line:95%,end
I've had it with the hat situation.

00:19:06.245 --> 00:19:10.749 line:95%,end
I don't have 48 more hours to
tell each kid 100 more times

00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:11.884 line:95%,end
how to wear their hat.

00:19:12.317 --> 00:19:16.221 line:95%,end
A hat is very specific to
the style of the routine.

00:19:16.755 --> 00:19:18.957 line:95%,end
Put the hat on their head
and make sure it's right.

00:19:19.458 --> 00:19:22.094 line:5%,start
JILL: That's not the way
to approach a situation.

00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:26.632 line:5%,start
I think the kids get the point.
But, come on, situations happen.

00:19:26.698 --> 00:19:30.569 line:95%,end
A hat may drop on the floor. Big deal.

00:19:30.936 --> 00:19:32.704 line:95%,end
One, two, three.

00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:35.107 line:95%,end
Bop!

00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:36.308 line:95%,end
Get it down.

00:19:36.408 --> 00:19:38.443 line:95%,end
Kendall is doing a jazz acrobatic routine.

00:19:38.510 --> 00:19:41.213 line:95%,end
Now this is a defining
moment in Kendall's life.

00:19:41.280 --> 00:19:42.381 line:95%,end
Right foot, rolling over.

00:19:42.447 --> 00:19:45.184 line:95%,end
She's either going to go
out there and wow the judges

00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:50.155 line:95%,end
and impress me or she's going
to go out there and blow it.

00:19:50.589 --> 00:19:53.759 line:95%,end
JILL: Even though Abby's been
really, really hard on Kendall

00:19:53.926 --> 00:19:57.296 line:95%,end
and it has not been an easy
road, I'm really proud of her.

00:19:57.362 --> 00:19:59.198 line:95%,end
She's working towards something
and she's seeing results.

00:19:59.298 --> 00:20:02.134 line:95%,end
This is this is really good.

00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:03.969 line:95%,end
ABBY: Kendall, you're marking things.

00:20:04.136 --> 00:20:05.504 line:95%,end
Why are you marking things?

00:20:05.671 --> 00:20:06.905 line:95%,end
I didn't give Maddie a solo.

00:20:07.306 --> 00:20:10.976 line:95%,end
If I did, she wouldn't be marking it.
She would do it full out every time.

00:20:11.043 --> 00:20:14.880 line:95%,end
I think sometimes Abby forgets
that Kendall is only nine years old.

00:20:15.013 --> 00:20:17.916 line:95%,end
I am so happy that Kendall
has a solo this week.

00:20:17.983 --> 00:20:20.085 line:95%,end
ABBY: Your face is
ridiculous on the turns.

