00:32:44.429 --> 00:32:46.431 line:95%,end
goes to-- drumroll, please.

00:32:46.497 --> 00:32:48.766 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:32:50.001 --> 00:32:52.870 line:95%,end
Number 131-A, "True Colors."

00:32:52.937 --> 00:32:55.139 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:32:55.206 --> 00:32:58.276 line:95%,end
ABBY: I have never been more
disappointed with my team.

00:32:58.376 --> 00:33:03.281 line:95%,end
Last week they were fourth, and now
nobody even places except Kendall.

00:33:03.381 --> 00:33:04.749 line:95%,end
And she's third.

00:33:05.216 --> 00:33:07.986 line:95%,end
Nia, Chloe, you picked
the wrong week to choke.

00:33:08.553 --> 00:33:10.321 line:95%,end
[door slams]

00:33:12.056 --> 00:33:13.958 line:95%,end
Well, well, well.

00:33:14.025 --> 00:33:16.661 line:95%,end
I didn't pick three soloists to come here

00:33:16.728 --> 00:33:21.332 line:95%,end
to put you in the competition
for you not to do well.

00:33:22.567 --> 00:33:26.170 line:95%,end
The thing that takes the work, the sweat

00:33:26.337 --> 00:33:28.606 line:95%,end
when is the last time
that you went into a class

00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:31.843 line:95%,end
and actually were dripping with sweat?

00:33:31.909 --> 00:33:35.980 line:95%,end
When is the last time your feet
were so blistery on the bottom

00:33:36.047 --> 00:33:37.315 line:95%,end
that they were cracked open and bleeding?

00:33:37.382 --> 00:33:38.950 line:95%,end
When was the last time that happened?

00:33:39.017 --> 00:33:40.618 line:95%,end
That's a dancer.

00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:43.554 line:95%,end
This group routine has to be perfect.

00:33:43.621 --> 00:33:45.823 line:95%,end
Nobody better drop a hat.

00:33:45.923 --> 00:33:50.261 line:95%,end
We need every point we can get
if we have a chance to beat Cathy.

00:33:50.328 --> 00:33:53.765 line:95%,end
And you all know how I
get when Cathy shows up.

00:33:54.699 --> 00:33:56.467 line:95%,end
That was an embarrassment.


00:33:59.103 --> 00:34:01.472 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:34:01.739 --> 00:34:03.875 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:34:03.941 --> 00:34:07.478 line:95%,end
Nobody placed in the solos except Kendall,
and she was only third.

00:34:07.545 --> 00:34:11.682 line:5%,start
These girls better do
the group dance perfect.

00:34:11.749 --> 00:34:13.618 line:95%,end
Think about Cathy beating us.

00:34:13.684 --> 00:34:16.654 line:95%,end
Think about your reputation
as the National Champions.

00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:19.791 line:95%,end
We can't lose to Cathy not now, not ever.

00:34:19.857 --> 00:34:24.829 line:95%,end
You got picked to do a job
to beat a bunch of girls who come out

00:34:24.896 --> 00:34:26.264 line:95%,end
and do a whole lot of nothing.

00:34:26.330 --> 00:34:30.635 line:95%,end
Don't embarrass yourself. More importantly
do not embarrass me out there.

00:34:30.701 --> 00:34:31.769 line:95%,end
Come on, let's go.

00:34:31.836 --> 00:34:33.104 line:5%,start
I love "Pink Lemonade."

00:34:33.204 --> 00:34:35.273 line:5%,start
I think it's probably one
of my favorite group dances

00:34:35.339 --> 00:34:36.808 line:95%,end
I've ever seen the girls put together.

00:34:36.874 --> 00:34:39.877 line:95%,end
I think it really has a lot of potential

00:34:39.944 --> 00:34:42.747 line:95%,end
but I don't know if it has potential
to beat an all boys team.

00:34:44.048 --> 00:34:48.052 line:5%,start
ANNOUNCER: Next up, please welcome
number 232-A, dancing to "Own It."

00:34:48.219 --> 00:34:51.189 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:34:53.591 --> 00:34:55.593 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:35:04.969 --> 00:35:08.005 line:95%,end
(SINGING) To know me is to
feel the love, feel the...

00:35:08.172 --> 00:35:12.176 line:95%,end
asteroid, outer space,
moving at a fast pace.

00:35:12.243 --> 00:35:14.112 line:95%,end
Timeline's down, down.

00:35:14.178 --> 00:35:16.047 line:95%,end
Every breath you try to take.

00:35:16.114 --> 00:35:19.417 line:95%,end
We gain sanity, split personality.

00:35:19.584 --> 00:35:20.918 line:95%,end
Oh, oh, oh.

00:35:20.985 --> 00:35:22.920 line:95%,end
Oh, oh, oh.

00:35:23.354 --> 00:35:25.022 line:95%,end
Own it. See it.

00:35:25.089 --> 00:35:26.691 line:95%,end
Dream it in the night.

00:35:26.757 --> 00:35:28.426 line:95%,end
Your possessors of your mind.

00:35:28.593 --> 00:35:30.394 line:95%,end
Move it here to bring you life.

00:35:30.561 --> 00:35:31.729 line:95%,end
Own it.

00:35:31.896 --> 00:35:35.733 line:95%,end
See you dancing in the yard,
DJs mixing on the roof.

00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:37.869 line:95%,end
One more shout out, then goodbye.

00:35:38.035 --> 00:35:41.873 line:95%,end
We gained sanity, split personality.

00:35:42.039 --> 00:35:43.374 line:95%,end
Own it.

00:35:43.541 --> 00:35:47.111 line:95%,end
From the outside, looking in,
grab the wheel and give a spin.

00:35:47.178 --> 00:35:49.680 line:5%,start
It's your time. Go out and win.

00:35:49.947 --> 00:35:52.550 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:35:59.690 --> 00:36:02.293 line:95%,end
JILL: It is crowd appeal at its best.

00:36:02.360 --> 00:36:04.795 line:95%,end
Are they working well together? No.

00:36:04.896 --> 00:36:06.998 line:5%,start
Was the crowd going nuts? Yes.

00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:08.900 line:5%,start
Were they better than our girls?

00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:11.836 line:5%,start
I'm not so sure, at this point.

00:36:12.470 --> 00:36:15.673 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: Up next to the stage,
please welcome number 215

00:36:15.973 --> 00:36:17.742 line:95%,end
"Pink Lemonade."

00:36:17.842 --> 00:36:20.278 line:5%,start
[cheering and applause]

00:36:24.348 --> 00:36:27.318 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:36:36.894 --> 00:36:43.301 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Life's a soiree
serving pink lemonade

00:36:43.701 --> 00:36:47.438 line:95%,end
a cascade of champagne.

00:36:48.072 --> 00:36:51.008 line:95%,end
You and me.

00:36:51.776 --> 00:36:58.749 line:95%,end
Life is a play and the star on Broadway

00:36:58.816 --> 00:37:04.855 line:95%,end
is you.

00:37:07.758 --> 00:37:11.362 line:95%,end
Just serve yourself.

00:37:14.732 --> 00:37:18.703 line:95%,end
ABBY: There's Chloe's hat, right smack
in front of the judges' face.

00:37:18.869 --> 00:37:25.509 line:95%,end
(SINGING) pink lemonade today.

00:37:33.751 --> 00:37:37.154 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:37:41.726 --> 00:37:45.363 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: I know the wrath of Abby's crazy,

00:37:45.429 --> 00:37:47.632 line:95%,end
"I want to beat Cathy's
all boy team," behavior


00:37:47.698 --> 00:37:50.001 line:95%,end
is going to come down on that one moment.

00:37:50.067 --> 00:37:52.737 line:95%,end
And there's nothing I can do
about it, and I feel helpless.

00:37:52.803 --> 00:37:55.906 line:95%,end
- Now my kid's going to get screamed at.
- They're all going to get screamed at.

00:37:55.973 --> 00:37:58.643 line:95%,end
- No, but pick on Chloe, especially.
- I can't stand it.

00:37:58.709 --> 00:38:00.611 line:95%,end
I can't stand that I have to
sit here and wait for this woman

00:38:00.711 --> 00:38:02.179 line:95%,end
to come in here and berate us.

00:38:02.246 --> 00:38:04.582 line:95%,end
[applause] Good job!

00:38:04.649 --> 00:38:08.886 line:95%,end
Just so you know, Abby is going to come
in here it's going to be awful.

00:38:11.622 --> 00:38:14.392 line:95%,end
- Nice job, Chloe!
- Huh?

00:38:14.725 --> 00:38:15.960 line:95%,end
- Nice job.
- Let's go. We're leaving.

00:38:16.093 --> 00:38:17.428 line:95%,end
You want Chloe gone, we're going.

00:38:17.495 --> 00:38:18.929 line:95%,end
You get your way.
You can have whoever you...

00:38:18.996 --> 00:38:20.865 line:95%,end
Walks out, falls all over
the place with the turns.

00:38:20.931 --> 00:38:22.233 line:95%,end
- CHRISTI: No, she didn't.
- And then drops her hat.

00:38:22.400 --> 00:38:23.668 line:95%,end
- Yes, she did.
- CHRISTI: No, she didn't.

00:38:23.734 --> 00:38:24.735 line:95%,end
ABBY: Yes, she did.
CHRISTI: You know what?

00:38:24.835 --> 00:38:27.371 line:95%,end
You go ahead and replace me. I'm leaving.
I'm not going to make a scene with you.

00:38:27.438 --> 00:38:29.140 line:95%,end
ABBY: Oh, that's the easy way out. Right?
- No.

00:38:29.206 --> 00:38:30.574 line:95%,end
I'm done. I'm done.

00:38:30.641 --> 00:38:32.910 line:95%,end
This is not what I signed up for
humiliation for my daughter.

00:38:32.977 --> 00:38:34.145 line:95%,end
I didn't humiliate her!
CHRISTI: Yes, you did.

00:38:34.245 --> 00:38:35.346 line:95%,end
She humiliated herself when she--

00:38:35.513 --> 00:38:36.614 line:95%,end
Abby, shut up.
ABBY: --fell out of the turn!

00:38:36.681 --> 00:38:38.282 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Shut up. Stop talking, now.

00:38:38.349 --> 00:38:40.351 line:95%,end
Replace us, that's fine. Come on, Chlo.

00:38:40.418 --> 00:38:41.986 line:95%,end
We're done.

00:38:42.153 --> 00:38:43.921 line:95%,end
[chatter]

00:38:44.088 --> 00:38:46.324 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Get away from me!

00:38:47.291 --> 00:38:50.594 line:95%,end
[ominous music]

00:38:50.795 --> 00:38:54.865 line:95%,end
I thought besides somebody
dropping their hat, it was not bad.

00:38:54.932 --> 00:38:57.568 line:5%,start
KELLY: I think that more is
going on in Christi's head

00:38:57.735 --> 00:39:01.906 line:5%,start
than just Abby yelling at
Chloe for her losing her hat.

00:39:01.972 --> 00:39:04.475 line:95%,end
I mean, there's been a lot going
on this competition season.

00:39:04.642 --> 00:39:07.678 line:95%,end
And I just think that we're all
a little stressed right now.

00:39:07.878 --> 00:39:10.748 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Get away from me.
Get away from me.

00:39:10.815 --> 00:39:13.317 line:95%,end
See ya, Christi.
I mean, what are you thinking?

00:39:13.384 --> 00:39:14.919 line:95%,end
Am I going to reprimand Chloe?

00:39:14.985 --> 00:39:17.221 line:95%,end
Am I going to tell her what she did wrong?
You bet.

00:39:18.556 --> 00:39:20.391 line:95%,end
Chloe, you just blew this.

00:39:20.825 --> 00:39:23.160 line:95%,end
If we don't win, it's your
fault for dropping the hat.

00:39:23.661 --> 00:39:26.831 line:5%,start
ANNOUNCER: The next category
is Junior Advanced Small Group.

00:39:26.931 --> 00:39:28.799 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Okay. Here we go.

00:39:29.166 --> 00:39:34.271 line:95%,end
My second runner up, number 214,
"The Lord of Gymnastics and Cheer."

00:39:34.405 --> 00:39:35.840 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:39:35.940 --> 00:39:40.144 line:95%,end
Separating my runner up and
my winner is 1/10 of a point.

00:39:40.544 --> 00:39:41.679 line:95%,end
Of course!

00:39:41.846 --> 00:39:45.716 line:95%,end
If Cathy beats me again
by 1/10 of a point--

00:39:52.490 --> 00:39:55.826 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: Number 232-A, "Own It,"
from Candy Apples Dance Center.

00:39:55.893 --> 00:39:57.728 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:39:57.895 --> 00:40:00.598 line:95%,end
And the winner of the Junior Advanced
Small Group

00:40:00.664 --> 00:40:02.800 line:95%,end
goes to number 215.

00:40:02.867 --> 00:40:05.369 line:5%,start
[cheering and applause]

00:40:06.437 --> 00:40:08.973 line:95%,end
MELISSA: It was the best
feeling in the world.

00:40:09.039 --> 00:40:13.344 line:5%,start
I can't even tell you how
good it felt to beat boys.

00:40:13.411 --> 00:40:18.416 line:95%,end
Where do we dance, ladies?
Abby Lee Dance Company!

00:40:18.516 --> 00:40:20.217 line:95%,end
I'm really excited that we beat Cathy

00:40:20.518 --> 00:40:22.653 line:95%,end
but it's just not the
same without Christi here.

00:40:22.820 --> 00:40:25.823 line:95%,end
If Abby would've realized
that Chloe dropping her hat

00:40:25.990 --> 00:40:29.727 line:95%,end
didn't ruin the number, I just think
the whole fight would've never happened.

00:40:29.794 --> 00:40:31.228 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I need a cab.

00:40:31.395 --> 00:40:34.398 line:95%,end
Do you know where I can find a cab?
Thank you.

00:40:34.565 --> 00:40:35.566 line:95%,end
Abby gets her way.

00:40:35.733 --> 00:40:37.601 line:95%,end
She's wanted to be gone for years,

00:40:37.668 --> 00:40:39.937 line:95%,end
and she doesn't think Chloe
has any kind of talent.

00:40:40.471 --> 00:40:42.106 line:95%,end
But somebody out there is
going to think she goes.

00:40:42.406 --> 00:40:43.841 line:95%,end
All right, kiddo, let's go outside.

00:40:44.508 --> 00:40:47.077 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:40:48.946 --> 00:40:51.248 line:95%,end
I'm so glad we beat them!

00:40:51.315 --> 00:40:54.285 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Come on.
We did not sign up for this.

00:40:54.351 --> 00:40:56.554 line:95%,end
I don't really think
this is worth it anymore.

00:41:03.127 --> 00:41:04.829 line:95%,end
ABBY (VOICEOVER): Next on "Dance Moms"--

00:41:04.895 --> 00:41:07.131 line:95%,end
Did you come in the big
crappy bus from Pittsburgh?

00:41:07.331 --> 00:41:10.434 line:5%,start
- Cathy, go to hell!
- Oh, you're just scared!

00:41:10.868 --> 00:41:13.938 line:5%,start
- You cannot talk to children like that.
- No, her.

00:41:14.004 --> 00:41:16.674 line:5%,start
But we have to beat those kids.
We have to.

00:41:17.475 --> 00:41:20.311 line:5%,start
- Cathy, no one wants you here.
- Just shut your mouth!

00:41:20.377 --> 00:41:22.213 line:5%,start
JILL: Shut your mouth! Woo!

00:41:22.279 --> 00:41:23.481 line:5%,start
ABBY: I didn't mean to do that.

00:41:23.547 --> 00:41:25.983 line:5%,start
Because I didn't mean to do that, either.

00:41:26.150 --> 00:41:29.520 line:5%,start
- ABBY: That woman just hit me.
- JILL: Come on, bring it on!

00:41:29.854 --> 00:41:31.388 line:5%,start
That's enough. Let's go outside.

00:41:31.622 --> 00:41:33.457 line:5%,start
Get lost, bitch!

